## US-010: Post-init agent management

### `hive add <name>`
- Options: `--agent <file>`, `--poll <seconds>`, `--budget <usd>`, `--daily-max <usd>`, `--description <text>`
- Validates name uniqueness and role tag collision
- Creates git worktree and branch (`agent/<name>`)
- Registers hooks (`.claude/settings.json`) in the worktree
- Updates `config.yaml` with comment preservation using `yaml` `parseDocument`
- Adds role mapping to chat config

### `hive remove <name>`
- Options: `--force` (remove running agent), `--delete-branch` (delete git branch)
- Refuses to remove running agents unless `--force` is passed
- Kills tmux window and process, releases lock
- Removes worktree (optionally deletes branch)
- Updates `config.yaml` (removes agent + role map entry)
- Cleans up state files (lock, checkpoint, spend)

### Other changes
- **`init.ts`**: Error message now references `hive add <name>` instead of manual YAML editing
- **`worktree.ts`**: Error message now references `hive remove` alongside `git worktree remove`
- **`completion.ts`**: Added `add` and `remove` completions for bash, zsh, and fish

### Quality gates
- `npm run typecheck` — passed
- `npm test` — 122 tests passed (6 suites)
- `npm run build` — passed

